<A NAME="eolPage67"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	The Female Health Company
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="C894-20160930X10K_HTM_NOTES">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Notes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Other comprehensive income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	:&nbsp;&nbsp;Accounting principles generally require that recognized revenue, expenses, gains and losses be included in net income.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although certain changes in assets and liabilities, such as foreign currency translation adjustments, are reported as a separate component of the equity section of the accompanying consolidated balance sheets, these items, along with net income, are components of comprehensive income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The U.S. parent company and its U.K. subsidiary routinely purchase inventory produced by its Malaysia subsidiary for sale to their respective customers. These intercompany trade accounts are eliminated in consolidation. The Company&#x2019;s policy and intent is to settle the intercompany trade account on a current basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since the U.K. and Malaysia subsidiaries adopted the U.S. dollar as their functional currencies effective October 1, 2009, no foreign currency gains or losses from intercompany trade are recognized.&nbsp;&nbsp;In fiscal 2016, 2015, and 2014, comprehensive income is equivalent to the reported net income.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Recently issued accounting pronouncements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	:&nbsp;&nbsp;In November 2015, the Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB) issued ASU 2015-17, Income Taxes (Topic 740): Balance Sheet Classification of Deferred Taxes.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments in this Update require that deferred tax liabilities and assets be classified as non-current in a classified statement of financial position.&nbsp;&nbsp;Current accounting principles require an entity to separate deferred income tax liabilities and assets into current and non-current amounts in a classified statement of financial position.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2015-17 will be effective for the Company beginning on October 1, 2017.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In May 2014, the FASB issued ASU 2014-09 &#x201C;Revenue from Contracts with Customers&#x201D; (Topic 606).&nbsp;&nbsp;This new accounting guidance on revenue recognition provides for a single five-step model to be applied to all revenue contracts with customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The new standard also requires additional financial statement disclosures that will enable users to understand the nature, amount, timing and uncertainty of revenue and cash flows relating to customer contracts.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2014-09 will be effective for the Company beginning on October 1, 2018.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are currently evaluating the impact of the new guidance on our consolidated financial statements and have not yet selected a transition approach to implement the standard.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In July 2015, the FASB issued ASU 2015-11, Inventory (Topic 330): Simplifying the Measurement of Inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;This new accounting guidance more clearly articulates the requirements for the measurement and disclosure of inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic 330, Inventory, currently requires an entity to measure inventory at the lower of cost or market.&nbsp;&nbsp;Market could be replacement cost, net realizable value, or net realizable value less an approximately normal profit margin.&nbsp;&nbsp;This new accounting guidance requires the measurement of inventory at the lower of cost or net realizable value.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2015-11 will be effective for the Company beginning on October 1, 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;The adoption of this guidance is not expected to have a material impact on our consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In February 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-02, Leases (Topic 842).&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments in this Update increase transparency and comparability among organizations by recognizing lease assets and lease liabilities on the balance sheet and disclosing key information about leasing arrangements.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2016-02 will be effective for the Company beginning on October 1, 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are currently evaluating the impact of the new guidance on our consolidated financial statements and have not yet selected a transition approach to implement the standard.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In March 2016, the FASB issued ASU 2016-09, Compensation &#x2013; Stock Compensation (Topic 718): Improvements to Employee Share-Based Payment Accounting.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amendments in this Update simplify the income tax effects, minimum statutory tax withholding requirements and impact of forfeitures related to how share-based payments are accounted for and presented in the financial statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;ASU 2016-09 will be effective for the Company beginning on October 1, 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are currently evaluating the impact of the new guidance on our consolidated financial statements and have not yet selected a transition approach to implement the standard.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:27PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note 2.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Earnings per Share
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Basic EPS is computed by dividing net income by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding for the period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Diluted EPS is computed by dividing net income by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding during the period after giving effect to all dilutive potential common shares that were outstanding during the period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Dilutive potential common shares consist of the incremental common shares issuable upon the exercise of stock options and unvested shares granted to employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and directors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

</FONT>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On August 1, 2015, the Company entered into an amendment to the Second
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Amended and Restated Loan Agree
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ment (as amended, the Loan Agreement) with Midland States Bank to extend the term of the Company&#x2019;s revolving line of credit to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	August 1, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The credit facility consisted of a single revolving note for up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	million with Midland States Bank, with borrowings limited to a borrowing base determined based on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	70
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	percent to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	80
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	percent of eligible accounts receivable plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	percent of eligible inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;Significant restrictive covenants in the Loan Agreement included prohibitions on any merger, consolidation or sale of all or a substantial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	portion of the Compa
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ny&#x2019;s assets, and limits on the payment of dividends or the repurchase of shares.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Loan Agreement did not con
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	tain any financial covenants that required compliance with ratios or amounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;Dividends and share repurchases were permitted as long as after giving effect to the dividend or share repurchase the Company had a ratio of total liabilities to total stockholders&#x2019; equity of no more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1:1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;Borrowings on the revolving note were to bear interest at the national prime rate published by the Wall Street Journal (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3.25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	percent at September 30, 2015).&nbsp;&nbsp;The note was collateralized by substantially all of the assets of the Company.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	No
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	amounts were outstanding under the revolving note at September 30, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	The Female Health Company
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="C894-20160930X10K_HTM_NOTES">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Notes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On December 29, 2015, the Company entered into a Credit Agreement (the Credit Agreement) with BMO Harris Bank N.A. (BMO Harris Bank).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Credit Agreement provides the Company with a revolving line of credit of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	million with a term that extends to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December 29, 2017
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Borrowings under the Credit Agreement bear interest, at the Company&#x2019;s option, at a base rate or at LIBOR plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2.25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company is also required to pay a commitment fee at the rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	0.10%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	per annum on the average daily unused portion of the revolving line of credit.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company's obligations under the Credit Agreement are secured by a lien against substantially all of the assets of the Company and a pledge of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	65%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	of the outstanding shares of The Female Health Company Limited.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to other customary representations, covenants and default provisions, the Company is required to maintain a minimum tangible net worth and to not to exceed a maximum total leverage ratio.&nbsp;&nbsp;Among the non-financial covenants, the Company is restricted in its ability to pay dividends, buy back shares of its common stock, incur additional debt and make acquisitions above certain
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	amounts.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	No
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	amounts were outstanding under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the Credit Agreement at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	September 30, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 1.5PT 0PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:105%;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The completion of the merger transaction with APP (see note 14) resulted in a default in FHC's compliance with certain covenants in the Credit Agreement and will constitute an "event of default" under the Credit Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 1.5PT 0PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:105%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 1.5PT 0PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:105%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On November
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	28,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016, FHC, Badger Acquisition Sub, Inc., APP and BMO Harris Bank entered into a Third Amendment to the Credit Agreement (the Amendment).&nbsp;&nbsp;Pursuant to the Amendment, BMO Harris Bank waived the defaults in FHC's compliance with the covenants in the Credit Agreement as a result of the completion of the merger transaction with APP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	APP became a co-borrower under the Credit Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As a result,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	the revolving line of credit remains in effect under the terms of the Credit Agreement until the end of its term on December 29, 2017
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:34PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Operating Leases and Rental Expense
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	leases
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	6,600
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	square feet of office space located in Chicago, Illinois. On May 11, 2016, the Company signed a new lease, effective November 1, 2016, for this office space for a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	seven
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	year period commencing on November 1, 2016 and ending on October 31, 2023.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lease grants the Company a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	seven
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	month lease holiday beginning November 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016, a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	month lease abatement beginning June 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2017, and provides a tenant improvement allowance.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lease requires escalating monthly payments ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5,833
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$9,285
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, plus real estate taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, utilities and maintenance expenses from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	June
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	to October 31, 20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	23
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company also has a renewal option to extend the term of the lease for a period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	years.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on the terms of the lease agreement, the Company was required to make a security deposit of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$55,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	year lease period from November 1, 2011 and ended on October 31, 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lease payment for October 2016 was recorded in September 2016.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:27PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note 6.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Income Taxes
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company accounts for income taxes using the liability method, which requires the recognition of deferred tax assets or liabilities for the tax-effected temporary differences between the financial reporting and tax bases of assets and liabilities, and for net operating loss and tax credit carryforwards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company completes a detailed analysis of its deferred income tax valuation allowance on an annual basis or more frequently if information comes to our attention that would indicate that a revision to its estimates is necessary.&nbsp;&nbsp;In evaluating the Company&#x2019;s ability to realize its deferred tax assets, management considers all available positive and negative evidence on a country by country basis, including past operating results and forecast of future taxable income.&nbsp;&nbsp;In determining future taxable income, management makes assumptions to forecast U.S. federal and state, U.K. and Malaysia operating income, the reversal of temporary differences, and the implementation of any feasible and prudent tax planning strategies. These assumptions require significant judgment regarding the forecasts of the future taxable income in each tax jurisdiction, and are consistent with the forecasts used to manage the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	business. It should be noted that the Company realized significant losses through 2005 on a consolidated basis. Since fiscal year 2006, the Company has consistently generated taxable income on a consolidated basis, providing a reasonable future period in which the Company can reasonably expect to generate taxable income. In management&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	analysis to determine the amount of the deferred tax asset to recognize, management projected future taxable income for each tax jurisdiction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Although management uses the best information available, it is reasonably possible that the estimates used by the Company will be materially different from the actual results. These differences could have a material effect on the Company's future results of operations and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Income before income taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	was taxed by the following jurisdictions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	for the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	September 30, 2016, 2015, and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	, respectively, for income tax purposes expiring in years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	202
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	to 2027
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company's U.K. subsidiary has U.K. net operating loss carryforwards of approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	60,863,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	September 30, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	can be carried forward indefinitely to be used to offset future U.K. taxable income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The federal and state income tax
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	expense

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	any other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	deferred income taxes applicable to undistributed earnings of foreign subsidiaries because it is the present intention of management to reinvest the undistributed earning
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	ASC Topic&nbsp;740 prescribes a recognition threshold and measurement attribute for the financial statement recognition and measurement of a tax position taken or expected to be taken in a tax return. ASC Topic&nbsp;740 developed a two-step process to evaluate a tax position and also provides guidance on de-recognition, classification, interest and penalties, accounting in interim periods, disclosure, and transition.&nbsp;The Company has not recorded a reserve for any tax positions for which the ultimate deductibility is highly certain but for which there is uncertainty about the timing of such deductibility.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In March 2008, the Company&#x2019;s shareholders approved the 2008 Stock Incentive Plan which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	utilized to provide equity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	opportunities and performance&#x2013;based incentives to attract, retain and motivate those persons who make (or are expected to make) important contributions to the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;A total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million shares are available for issuance under the plan. As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	September 30, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, a total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1,471,302
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	had been granted under the plan and not forfeited or are subject to outstanding commitments to issue shares under the Plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	167,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares were in the form of stock options and the remainder were in the form of restricted stock or other share grants.&nbsp;

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Under the Company&#x2019;s previous share-based long-term incentive compensation plan, the 1997 Stock Option Plan, the Company granted non-qualified stock options to employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	, directors, and consultants
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. There are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	shares available for grant under this plan which expired on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	December 31, 2006
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Options issued under this plan expire
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	years after the date of grant and generally vested
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	1/36
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	per month, with full vesting after
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	years. Under the Company&#x2019;s 2008 Stock Incentive Plan, options issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	in May 2009
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	expire
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	years after the date of grant and vest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	1/36
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	per month, with full vesting after
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	17,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>

	years with vesting over a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	two
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	on the second anniversary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of the grant date.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company did not grant any options
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	during fiscal years 2015 or 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on the Company&#x2019;s history of prior forfeitures and future expectations it was determined that there would be no forfeiture rate used.

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	During the year ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	September 30, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the Company used historical volatility of our common stock over a period equal to the expected life of the options to estimate their fair value.&nbsp;&nbsp;The dividend yield assumption is based on the Company&#x2019;s history and expectation of future dividend payouts on the common stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;The risk-free interest rate is based on the implied yield available on U.S. treasury zero-coupon issues with an equivalent remaining term.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The expected term of the options represents the estimated period of time until exercise and is based on the simplified method.&nbsp;&nbsp;To value options granted for actual stock-based compensation, the Company used the Black-Scholes option valuation model.&nbsp;&nbsp;When the measurement date is certain, the fair value of each option grant is estimated on the date of grant and is based on the assumptions used for the expected stock price volatility, expected term, risk-free interest rates and future dividend payments.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

	, respectively.

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="C894-20160930X10K_HTM_NOTES">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Notes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:27PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note 8.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Stock Repurchase Program
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s Stock Repurchase Program was announced on January 17, 2007.&nbsp;&nbsp;At initiation, the plan&#x2019;s terms specified that up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares of its common stock could be purchased during the subsequent twelve months. Subsequently, the Board has amended the plan a number of times to both extend its term and increase the maximum number of shares which could be repurchased.&nbsp;&nbsp;Currently, the plan allows for a maximum repurchase of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares through the period ending December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;From the program&#x2019;s onset through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	September 30, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the total number of shares repurchased by the Company is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2,183,704
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Stock Repurchase Program authorizes purchases in privately negotiated transactions as well as in the open market.&nbsp;&nbsp;In October&nbsp;2008, the Company's Board of Directors authorized repurchases in private transactions under the Stock Repurchase Program of shares issued under the Company's equity compensation plans to directors, employees and other service providers at the market price on the effective date of the repurchase request. Total repurchases under this provision currently are limited to an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	450,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares per calendar year and to a maximum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	50,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares annually per individual.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Total repurchase transaction are as follows (in shares):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:27PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Note 9.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Employee Benefit Plan
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company has a Simple Individual Retirement Account (IRA) plan for its employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees are eligible to participate in the plan if their compensation reaches certain minimum levels and are allowed to contribute up to a maximum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$15,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	annual compensation to the plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has elected to match
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	percent of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	employee contributions to the plan up to a maximum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	percent of employee compensation for the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	September 30, 2016, 2015, and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Annual Company contributions were approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$33,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$37,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$31,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	for the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	September 30, 2016, 2015, and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In March 2014, the Company elected to contribute
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	percent into the personal pension schemes of certain senior U.K. employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Contributions for the years ended September 30, 2016, 2015, and 2014 were approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$23,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:23PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note 11.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:4PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Contingent Liabilities
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The testing, manufacturing and marketing of consumer products by the Company entail an inherent risk that product liability claims will be asserted against the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company maintains product liability insurance coverage for claims arising from the use of its products.&nbsp;&nbsp;The coverage amount is currently
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	million for FHC's consumer health care product.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL NARROW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; PADDING-RIGHT:34PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 1.5PT 0PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:105%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Under the terms of the Amended Merger Agreement, the outstanding shares of APP common stock and preferred stock were converted into the right to receive in the aggregate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of the Company's common stock and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	546,756
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	shares of the Company's Class A Convertible Preferred Stock - Series 4 (the Series 4 Preferred Stock).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0.5PT 1.5PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 1.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2,585,379
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares of the Company's common stock to Torreya Capital, the Company's financial advisor (the Financial Advisor Warrant).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Financial Advisor Warrant has a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-year term, a cashless exercise feature and a strike price equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1.93
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	per share, the average price of the Company's common stock for the ten-day period preceding the original announcement of the APP Merger on April 6, 2016. The fair value of the Financial Advisor Warrant is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$723,906
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	based on the average closing price of the Company's common stock for the five days prior to October 31, 2016 of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$1.02
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Financial Advisor Warrant was vested upon issuance.
</FONT>

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	760,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares to a member of the Company's board of directors and a consultant.&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	One
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-half of these stock awards consist of restricted stock and stock options which vest on the first anniversary of the grant date and the other half of these stock awards consist of restricted stock units and stock appreciation rights that vest on the second anniversary of the grant date.&nbsp;&nbsp;The restricted stock units and stock appreciation rights will be settled in the Company's common stock if, prior to the vesting date, the Company receives shareholder approval under the NASDAQ listing rules to (i) increase the number of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	authorized
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shares under the 2008 Stock Incentive Plan sufficient to issue such shares or (ii) adopt a new plan under which such shares would be issued. If such approval is not received by the vesting date, such awards will be settled in cash based on the fair market value of the Company's common stock on the vesting date in the case of the restricted stock units and on the exercise date in the case of the stock appreciation rights.&nbsp;&nbsp;The fair value of these awards is approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$722,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and they have a weighted average life of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5.75
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	years.

	As soon as reasonably practicable, but in no event later than thirty (30) days after the Closing Date, Borrower shall deliver to the Bank: (i) the original stock certificate evidencing Borrower&#x2019;s shares in The Female Health Company Limited, a company organized under the laws of the United Kingdom pledged to the Bank pursuant to the Pledge Agreement; and (ii) a true and correct copy of all filed stamped UCC termination statements evidencing the due termination of all liens against Borrower and/or Borrower&#x2019;s assets.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	4.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Except as specifically amended herein, the Credit Agreement shall continue in full force and effect in accordance with its original terms. Reference to this specific First Amendment need not be made in the Credit Agreement, the Security Agreement, the Pledge Agreement, the Note, the Loan Documents, or any other instrument or document executed in connection therewith, or in any certificate, letter or communication issued or made pursuant to or with respect to the Credit Agreement, any reference in any of such items to the Credit Agreement being sufficient to refer to the Credit Agreement as amended hereby.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	4.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Borrower agrees to pay on demand all costs and expenses of or incurred by the Lenders and/or Lender in connection with the negotiation, preparation, execution and delivery of this First Amendment, including the fees and expenses of counsel for the Lenders and/or Lender, which have not been included and paid pursuant to

	hereof.

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	4.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	This First Amendment may be executed in any number of counterparts, and by the different parties on different counterpart signature pages, all of which taken together shall constitute one and the same agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any of the parties hereto may execute this First Amendment by signing any such counterpart and each of such counterparts shall for all purposes be deemed to be an original. Delivery of executed counterparts of this First Amendment by telecopy shall be effective as an original. This First Amendment shall be governed by the internal laws of the State of Illinois.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	4.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	For value received, including without limitation, the agreements of Lender in this First Amendment, Borrower hereby releases the Lender, and each of its current and former shareholders, directors, officers, agents, employees, attorneys, consultants, and professional advisors (collectively, the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Released Parties
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;) of and from any and all demands, actions, causes of action, suits, controversies, acts and omissions, liabilities, and other claims of every kind or nature whatsoever, both in law and in equity, known or unknown, which Borrower has or ever had against the Released Parties, including, without limitation, those arising out of the existing financing arrangements between Borrower and Lender, and Borrower further acknowledges that, as of the date hereof, it does not have any counterclaim, set-off, or defense against the Released Parties, each of which Borrower hereby expressly waives.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 100%;TEXT-INDENT:36PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	4.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#222222;FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Without in any way limiting any provision herein, the Credit Agreement, or any other Loan Document, Borrower hereby indemnifies and hold harmless the Released Parties from, and shall pay to Lender, on behalf of and for the benefit of itself, or on behalf of and for the benefit of Released Parties, or any one of them, as the case may be, the amount of, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#222222;FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	reimburse the Released Parties for, any Loss that the Released Parties or any of them may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#222222;FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	suffer, sustain, or become subject to, as a result of, in connection with, or in any way relating to the pledge of the lost original stock certificate representing Borrower&#x2019;s ownership of equity interests in The Female Health Company Limited pledged to Midland States Bank, as successor in interest to Heartland Bank, any replacement stock certificate issued in lieu therefor, and the pledge of such replacement stock certificate as Collateral for Borrower&#x2019;s Obligations.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the purposes of this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#222222;FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section 4.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#222222;FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#222222;FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	"Loss" shall mean any cost, loss, liability, obligation, claim, cause of action, damage, deficiency, expense (including costs of investigation and defense and reasonable attorneys' fees and expenses), fine, penalty, judgment, award, assessment, or diminution of value.
</FONT>
</P>

	4.7

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The recitals and all exhibits and schedules hereto constitute an integral part of this First Amendment, evidencing the intent of the parties in executing this First Amendment and describing the circumstances surrounding its execution.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, the recitals, exhibits and schedules are, by this express reference, made a part of the covenants hereof, and this First Amendment shall be construed in the light thereof.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except as otherwise provided in this First Amendment, capitalized terms used herein without definition shall have the same meanings herein as such terms have in the Credit Agreement.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	This First Amendment shall not be construed more strictly against the Lender than against the Borrower merely by virtue of the fact that the same has been prepared by counsel for the Lender, it being recognized that the Borrower and the Lender have contributed substantially and materially to the preparation of this First Amendment, and the Borrower and Lender each acknowledges and waives any claim contesting the existence and the adequacy of the consideration given by the other in entering into this First Amendment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each of the parties to this First Amendment represents that it has been advised by its respective counsel of the legal and practical effect of this First Amendment, and recognizes that it is executing and delivering this First Amendment, intending thereby to be legally bound by the terms and provisions thereof, of its own free will, without promises or threats or the exertion of duress upon it.&nbsp;&nbsp;The signatories hereto state that they have read and understand this First Amendment, that they intend

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;;PADDING:0PT 23PT 0PT 0PT;">
	4.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Each of the Guarantors hereby consents to this Amendment and ratifies and affirms the Guaranty and agrees that the Guaranty is in full force and effect following the execution and delivery of this Amendment.&nbsp;&nbsp;The representations and warranties of each Guarantor in the Guaranty are, as of the date hereof, true and correct and no Guarantor knows of any default thereunder.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Guaranty continues to be the valid and binding obligation of each Guarantor, enforceable in accordance with its terms and no Guarantor has any claims or defenses to the enforcement of the rights and remedies of the Bank thereunder, except as provided in the Guaranty.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Guarantor further agrees that the consent of the Guarantors to any further amendments to the Credit Agreement shall not be required as a result of this consent having been obtained. Each of the undersigned acknowledges that the Bank is relying on the assurances provided in this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 4.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	in entering into the Amendment.

	5.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Each Borrower and each Guarantor and hereby acknowledges and agrees that the Liens created and provided for by the Collateral Documents continue to secure, among other things, the Obligations arising under the Credit Agreement; and the Collateral Documents and the rights and remedies of the Bank thereunder, the obligations of each Borrower and/or each Guarantor thereunder, and the Liens created and provided for thereunder remain in full force and effect and shall not be affected, impaired or discharged hereby. Nothing herein contained shall in any manner affect or impair the priority of the liens and security interests created and provided for by the Collateral Documents as to the indebtedness which would be secured thereby prior to giving effect to this Amendment.

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;COLOR:#010000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;;PADDING:0PT 24PT 0PT 0PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

	(c)
</FONT>

	evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant's disclosure controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

	(d)

	disclosed in this report any change in the registrant's internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant's most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant's fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant's internal control over financial reporting; and
</FONT>
